cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and their theoretical analysis. Specifically, it compares two types of learning algorithms - positive unlabeled (PU) learning and positive negative (PN) learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these algorithms in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Theoretical analysis of algorithms often involves the use of mathematical and statistical techniques, which could also place this paper in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
